body:
### expected behaviour
after entering ldap connection info (non-ssl) to my active directory server, i wanted to see a limited list of all ad users and have them log into owncloud

### actual behaviour
the users page seems to always detect "0 users" and eventually locks up. the logs appear to show that it's attempting to connect via ssl/tls even though i'm only using clear text and have specified port 389

### steps to reproduce
1. enter the ad server ip as the host, with port 389
2. enter the bind user, in my case this is "cn=ldapbind,ou=service_accounts,dc=domain,dc=com" along with the password
3. from there it won't detect any users and produces the log messages:
{"app":"user_ldap","message":"ldap error connect error (-11) after calling ldap_start_tls","level":0,"time":"2013-12-12t16:19:59+00:00"}
{"app":"user_ldap","message":"ldap error connect error (-11) after calling ldap_errno","level":0,"time":"2013-12-12t16:19:59+00:00"}


### server configuration
operating system:
ubuntu 12.04.3 lts

web server: 
apache 2

database:
mysql 5

php version:
5.3.10

owncloud version: (see owncloud admin page)
6

updated from an older owncloud or fresh install:
fresh

list of activated app:
ldap

the content of config/config.php: (without the database password and passwordsalt)
<?php
$config = array (
  'instanceid' => 'ocb485c72214',
  'passwordsalt' => 'xxxxxxxx',
  'datadirectory' => '/mnt/local/owncloud',
  'dbtype' => 'mysql',
  'version' => '6.0.0.13',
  'dbname' => 'owncloud',
  'dbhost' => 'localhost',
  'dbtableprefix' => 'oc_',
  'dbuser' => 'owncloud',
  'dbpassword' => 'xxxxxxxx',
  'installed' => true,
  'forcessl' => true,
  'ldapignorenamingrules' => false,
  'loglevel' => '0',
);

### client configuration
browser:
chrome

operating system:
windows 8.1

